{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480931"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:54:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:54:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"127"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/127"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.09,0.7,0.02,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"127"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92228"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/127"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"127"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75548"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"278"},{"type":"tags","id":"1453"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3552"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"9777"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"12330"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31136"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31137"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92228","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92228"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for counselling regarding surgical management of her obesity. She has a six-month history of weight plateau despite adherence to dietary and lifestyle modifications. She initially presented with a BMI of 42 kg/m\u00b2 and has now reached 36 kg/m\u00b2. Her medical history includes type 2 diabetes, hypertension, hyperlipidaemia, obstructive sleep apnoea, and gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. Her medications include metformin, esomeprazole, ramipril, and candesartan. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate bariatric procedure to recommend?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sleeve gastrectomy","Laparoscopic gastric band","Roux-en-Y gastric bypass","Intragastric balloon","Single anastomosis Duodeno-Ileal Bypass with Sleeve Gastrectomy (SADI-S)"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has obesity with multiple comorbidities including type 2 diabetes, hypertension, hyperlipidaemia, obstructive sleep apnoea, and importantly, gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD). When considering bariatric surgery options, the presence of GORD is a significant factor in procedure selection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERoux-en-Y gastric bypass\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate procedure for this patient. It produces effective and sustained weight loss while also being beneficial for patients with GORD. The procedure creates a small gastric pouch and bypasses part of the small intestine, which reduces acid reflux symptoms. Additionally, it offers excellent glycaemic control for patients with type 2 diabetes, often leading to significant improvement or remission of diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESleeve gastrectomy\u003C/strong\u003E is contraindicated in patients with symptomatic GORD as it can worsen reflux symptoms. This procedure removes approximately 80% of the stomach, creating a tube-like structure, but can increase intragastric pressure and exacerbate reflux. Despite being a commonly performed bariatric procedure with good weight loss outcomes, it would not be appropriate for this patient due to her pre-existing GORD.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaparoscopic gastric band\u003C/strong\u003E has fallen out of favour due to its long-term failure to maintain weight loss and high rate of complications requiring revision surgery. It involves placing an adjustable band around the upper portion of the stomach to create a small pouch. While it is reversible and adjustable, it has poorer long-term outcomes compared to other bariatric procedures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntragastric balloon\u003C/strong\u003E is a temporary, non-surgical weight loss device that is placed in the stomach endoscopically and typically removed after 6 months. It provides modest weight loss (typically 10-15% of total body weight) and is generally used as a bridge therapy or for patients with lower BMIs. It would be inadequate for this patient with a BMI of 36 kg/m\u00b2 and multiple comorbidities requiring more substantial and durable weight loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESingle anastomosis Duodeno-Ileal Bypass with Sleeve Gastrectomy (SADI-S)\u003C/strong\u003E is a modified version of the duodenal switch procedure that involves creating a sleeve gastrectomy and a single duodeno-ileal anastomosis. While effective for weight loss and metabolic improvement, it includes a sleeve component that could worsen this patient\u0027s GORD. Additionally, it carries higher risks of nutritional deficiencies and malabsorption compared to Roux-en-Y gastric bypass, making it less suitable as a first-line option for this patient.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Roux-en-Y gastric bypass is the preferred bariatric procedure for patients with gastro-oesophageal reflux disease and obesity.","Sleeve gastrectomy is contraindicated in patients with symptomatic gastro-oesophageal reflux disease.","Bariatric surgery should be considered for patients with BMI \u003E35 kg/m\u00b2 or \u003E30kg/m\u00b2 with obesity-related comorbidities who have not achieved weight loss goals with lifestyle interventions."],"references":["Arterburn D, Gupta A. Comparing the Outcomes of Sleeve Gastrectomy and Roux-en-Y Gastric Bypass for Severe Obesity. JAMA. 2018;319:235-37. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/293Public","Public Education Committee. Baratric Surgery Procedures. American Societey for Metaoblic and Baratric Surgery. 2021. Available at: https://asmbs.org/patients/bariatric-surgery-procedures/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75548"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"127"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75548","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75548"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-16T21:36:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-16T21:37:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"127"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92228"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":